post_cb({"13338478": {"ParentId": "13338329", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>Yes, <code>std::polar</code> is thread-safe (for some definition of thread-safe). See <code>[res.on.data.races]/3</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_13338329_13338478_0\">A C++ standard library function shall not directly or indirectly modify objects (1.10) accessible by threads other than the current thread unless the objects are accessed directly or indirectly via the function\u2019s non- const arguments, including this.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Since <code>std::polar</code> only takes const parameters, it does not modify any objects outside the thread that it is called from.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "485561", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "13338478", "Score": "4", "CreationDate": "2012-11-12T04:41:01.637", "LastActivityDate": "2012-11-12T04:41:01.637"}, "13338329": {"CommentCount": "2", "ViewCount": "154", "CreationDate": "2012-11-12T04:19:49.430", "LastActivityDate": "2012-11-12T04:41:01.637", "Title": "Is std::polar thread safe?", "AcceptedAnswerId": "13338478", "PostTypeId": "1", "Id": "13338329", "Score": "3", "Body": "<p>Is the function <code>std::polar()</code> thread safe?</p>\n<p>I would like to call the <code>#pragma</code> directive on a for that uses it inside.</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><pragma>", "OwnerUserId": "1353689", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_13338329_13338478_0": {"section_id": 6348, "quality": 0.8695652173913043, "length": 20}}, "n3337": {"so_13338329_13338478_0": {"section_id": 6105, "quality": 0.8695652173913043, "length": 20}}, "n4659": {"so_13338329_13338478_0": {"section_id": 7857, "quality": 0.8695652173913043, "length": 20}}}});